{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_66","type":"agent_message","text":"The isolated native repro exposed the first real cause: in a native executable, `HijrahChronology` crashes with `NullPointerException` when `java.home` is unset, because JDK 25’s static initializer now does `Path.of(StaticProperty.javaHome(), \"conf\", \"chronology\")`. I’m verifying whether the TCK’s native test launcher is actually propagating the configured `-Djava.home=...`; if it isn’t, the minimal fix is in the shared harness rather than `opencsv` metadata."}}
